			<ul>
				<li>
					<h3>Audio</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended for non-music audio files such as audio books and podcasts.</p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Documents</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended for document files such as word processing or .pdf files.</p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Favorites</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended for your favorite files.</p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Music</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended for music files such as those in .mp3 or .flac formats.</p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Pictures</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended for digital picture files in formats such as .jpg, .png, .gif.</p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Profile</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended as a place for you to store your personal profile images which is used to represent you to friends. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Public</h3>
					<p>This folder is a special folder whose contents are visible on your personal home page.  Note that if you place items in this folder, they will be visible to the outside world. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Research</h3>
					<p>This folder is intended as a place for you to store files related to research that you may be conducting. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Videos</h3>
					<p>This folder is used to store video images informats such as .mp4. </p>
				</li>

				<li>
					<h3>Trash</h3>
					<p>This is a special folder where items are moved after they have been deleted.  Deleted items may be recovered from the Trash until the trash is emptied, after which they are permanantly deleted. </p>
				</li>
			</ul>

		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-play"></i>The Run Menu</h2>
			<p>In the lower left corner, note the "Run" button. This displays a menu of apps that you can run to perform various tasks such as viewing images, browsing news, or playing music.</p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropup run menu" src="images/help/getting-started/using-desktop/run-menu@2x.png" />
